79.9	Padua	Padua	Padua stands on the Bacchiglione River, 40 km west of Venice and 29 km southeast of Vicenza. The Brenta River, which once ran through the city, still touches the northern districts. Its agricultural setting is the Venetian Plain . To the city's south west lies the Euganaean Hills, praised by Lucan and Martial, Petrarch, Ugo Foscolo, and Shelley.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Pratto_dela_Valle_Padova.jpg/250px-Pratto_dela_Valle_Padova.jpg
